{
  "doc_id": "20563",
  "text": "Up to our knowledge it is not possible to obtain exponential decay with only control of L p -norms on the initial data (even though we are not aware of an explicit counterexample). This is related to the main difficulty in analysing the decay rate; the entropy dissipation is too weak to produce a Poincaré inequality. We explain this in more details in Section 2. This is usual and the case of Fokker-Planck equations and \"hypocoercive\" equations are other examples [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
